   nn
</P>
<P>
   A Ghostly Sale Tale
</P>
<P>
   Steven King's first digital novella, ``Riding the Bullet,'' went
on sale and took in roughly 400,000 orders on the first day. The
ghost story _ available only as a download to computers, handheld
readers and Palm Pilots _ was sold for $2.50 or given away.
</P>
<P>
   Online booksellers had trouble meeting the extraordinary demand,
for which they were unprepared. But it boosted the credibility of
the e-book market. _ By DOREEN CARVAJAL
</P>
<P>
   Guns Don't Kill People, Presidents Do
</P>
<P>
   Wayne LaPierre, executive vice president of the National Rifle
Association said President Clinton tolerated a certain amount of
violence and killing to strengthen the case for gun control and to
score points for his party. Clinton called the comments ``smear
tactics.''
</P>
<P>
   Then LaPierre said Clinton had blood ``on his hands'' because he
had not enforced existing gun laws.
</P>
<P>
   Later in the week, Smith &AMP; Wesson agreed to install locks on its
handguns to make them more childproof, among several other gun
control measures. In return, Washington and local governments would
withdraw lawsuits seeking damages for gun violence.
</P>
<P>
   _ By ROBERT PEAR
</P>
<P>
   Eye for an Eye
</P>
<P>
   Federal prosecutors in New York have decided to pursue the death
penalty against at least one of the defendants in the bombings of
two U.S. embassies in Africa in 1998, which killed more than 200
people and injured thousands more.
</P>
<P>
   The decision by Mary Jo White, the U.S. district attorney, must
still be approved by Attorney General Janet Reno, which is
expected.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors say Mohamed Rashed Daoud al-'Owhali rode truck
carrying the bomb that blew up the embassy in Nairobi, Kenya, and
that he said the attack had been a ``martyrdom operation.''
</P>
<P>
   _ By BENJAMIN WEISER
</P>
<P>
   The Dawn Monkey
</P>
<P>
   Scientists announced the discovery of the smallest known
primate, an extinct animal no longer than a human thumb and
weighing less than an ounce.
</P>
<P>
   It is one of several species of Eosimias, (dawn monkey) that
lived 45 million years ago in a rain forest in what is now China.
These wee creatures appear to hold a key to a critical transition
in evolution.
</P>
<P>
   Examining fossils of the tiny ankle and foot bones,
paleontologists found strong evidence that the animal was the
earliest known higher primate, the lineage that led eventually to
human beings.
</P>
<P>
   _ By JOHN NOBLE WILFORD
</P>
<P>
   Whitewater Dries Up
</P>
<P>
   Robert W. Ray, the independent counsel for Whitewater matters,
filed a report on the Clinton White House's improper acquisition of
some 900 FBI files, many concerning prominent Republicans.
</P>
<P>
   Ray reported definitively: nothing illegal occurred. He also
began the endgame for the five-year investigation.
</P>
<P>
   Over the next few months, Ray will file two more final reports,
one on the firing of White House travel office employees, the other
about Whitewater matters.
</P>
<P>
   _ By NEIL LEWIS
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
