   GORE-WOMEN _ WASHINGTON _ The innermost circle of Vice President
Al Gore's advisers isn't to be found at the campaign headquarters
in Nashville, Tenn. Instead, it's his wife, Tipper, and his eldest
daughter, Karenna. The life story of Gore's mother, Pauline, also
is a centerpiece of his stump speeches. A look at how the women
surrounding Gore help shape his campaign and help attract the women
voters that are a key part of his White House strategy. (Shepard,
Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
