<P>
   F22 _ WASHINGTON _ The Georgia Congressional delegation is
preparing for war with California Republican Rep. Jerry Lewis over
funding for the F-22 fighter jet program. Lewis, chairman of the
defense appropriations committee, recently told lawmakers that the
``F-22 is a very, very expensive program.'' An opening salvo? A
repeat of last year's funding battle? After all, Lewis did convince
the House to nix funding for building the aircraft last year. Armed
with statistics that show Lewis is inflating the cost of the plane
and the Air Force's need for the plane, Georgia's lawmakers are
doing everything they can to protect the program. (Carr, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
