<P>
   CLINTON-INDIA _ WASHINGTON _ One is the mightiest democracy on
Earth; the other the most populous. One is the richest nation in
the history of the world; the other, one of its poorest. Both the
United States and India, though, are linked by a web of historical,
cultural and geopolitical ties that President Clinton hopes to
strengthen in a weeklong visit to the Indian subcontinent, the
first by a U.S. president since Jimmy Carter's visit 22 years ago.
(Deans, Cox News Service).
