   H. RAP BROWN FOLLOWS
</P>
<P>
   HRAP-MAIN _ ATLANTA _ News of the day in the search for former
black activist H. Rap Brown, known as Jamil Abdullah Al-Amin. One
sheriff's deputy was shot and killed and another wounded Thursday
night while trying to deliver a warrant against Brown. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   HRAP-PROFILE _ ATLANTA - Profile of H. Rap Brown.
(Auchmutey/Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HRAP-COP-PROFILES _ ATLANTA _ Profiles of the two Fulton County
Sheriff's deputies shot in Thursday's attack. One of them,
nine-year veteran Ricky Kinchen, has died. Trying to find out as
much as we can about these officers. (Suggs-Charles, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   HRAP-NEIGHBORHOOD _ ATLANTA _ The West End neighborhood has one
of the richest histories of any Atlanta community. In the 1970s --
with integrated institutions such as St. Athnony's Catholic Church
and Brown High School -- it was considered a rare bastion of
racially harmony in a period when many whites were moving to the
suburbs. By the early 1980s, West End had become a hub for black
activists and a thriving business district for AUC students and
black Southwest Atlanta residents. More recently, crime and poverty
have blighted the area but it remains a stronghold for community
activists and historic sites, such as Wren's Nest, the home of
Uncle Remus author Joel Chandler Harris. (Schneider, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   GORE-WOMEN _ WASHINGTON _ The innermost circle of Vice President
Al Gore's advisers isn't to be found at the campaign headquarters
in Nashville, Tenn. Instead, it's his wife, Tipper, and his eldest
daughter, Karenna. The life story of Gore's mother, Pauline, also
is a centerpiece of his stump speeches. A look at how the women
surrounding Gore help shape his campaign and help attract the women
voters that are a key part of his White House strategy. (Shepard,
Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
