<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0318: STARGAZER _ In a quiet mountain valley in
West Virginia, an enormous telescope is growing. The Green Bank
Telescope could let astronomers examine uncharted reaches of the
universe, and perhaps alter our conceptions of time and space and
creation. (Dart, Cox News Service). Art includes a 3-column color
overall photo of the telescope, a 2-column color photo of workers
placing panels in the telescope's dish, a 3-column photo of a
scientist involved in the project and an 18-pica color photo of an
American flag flying on top of the telescope.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   TAIWAN-ELECTIONS _ TAIPEI _ Spot coverage of the Taiwan
elections. Developing. (Chao, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Taiwan is 12 hours head of Eastern Standard Time. Moved
Saturday at 2 p.m., to be followed by a 1STLD by 9 p.m. EST.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-WINE _ TIJUANA, Mexico _ Tequila. Tequila. Tequila. There
are some 500 types and brands of the Mexican spirit available here.
As a result, wine-making has had a difficult time taking off over
the years. And when it did, the product was just plain bad. But
efforts to improve the quality of Mexico's wines have begun paying
off. With help from expert vintners from its neighbor to the north
_ California _ winemakers here are experiencing a mini-boom.
