<P>
   RUSSIA-COMMUNISTS _ TULA, Russia _ Despite the hype surrounding
Vladimir Putin, almost 50 percent of Russians are expected to vote
for other candidates in the upcoming presidential elections. Twelve
candidates are running in the race, and some of the strongest
opposition to Putin comes from the Communist Party rank-and-file
members, who disagree with Putin's views on relations with the
United States and on economic issues like land reform. In a
Communist bulwark town, regular Russians give their views about
politics and why they stand behind their man, candidate Gennady
Zyuganov. (Coker, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
