   BOTBALL _ RESTON, Va. _ At first glance, the pre-teens and
just-teens might look like a bunch of kids playing with toy robots.
But to the high-tech firms that pick up the tab for the regional
and national ``botball'' competitions, they're something far more
valuable: potential employees. In a mix of altruism and need for an
educable work force, high-tech firms are trying to influence
students' interests and choices at a younger and younger age. The
finals will be in Austin. (Mollison, Cox News Service). WITH
