give up the family fortune accumulated by her father, Francis, a
banking partner of J.P. Morgan's. Rather, she invested it in two of
the most abused groups in 19th-century America as she dared to
create a congregation of missionary nuns dedicated to educating
post-slavery blacks and American Indians. (Laura Pedrick/The New
