<P>
   &QL; 
IMMIGRATION _ Sixteen and pregnant, Renata Hajnos must have
pictured the ideal ending: fleeing her dirt-poor mountain village
in Poland for an idyllic new life with her lover in Chicago. But
early this month, Hajnos was intercepted with several other Poles
who entered the United States illegally near Nogales, Ariz. Her
case exemplifies a new trend: Eastern Europeans taking advantage of
Mexico's relaxed immigration policies to eventually enter the
United States. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
STADIUM _ The Arizona Cardinals learned a hard lesson last week in
the political reality of financing a new football stadium.
Lawmakers are in no mood to play ball unless the team _ or another
private source _ can carry a bigger chunk of the construction cost
for a proposed $341 million stadium. The Cardinals, who say they
generate fewer revenues from stadium operations than any team in
the NFL, maintain what lawmakers are asking for can't be done.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Undated) The economics of shared experience
allows even a hack like me to participate in the greatest
get-rich-quick scheme of all time. All a writer's got to do is
invest a little time and personal capital and the dividends come
pouring in. More often than not, I keep the proceeds for myself.
But after years of raking in the revenue, the vaults of my memory
are stuffed with the stories of others. It's time, this once, for a
little profit-sharing. By EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A''
and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
